e regarding these subjects. It indudes information on context and history, the provisions and requirements contained in French regulations and international agreements, as well as details of the roles played by the various entities involved, induding IRSN.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aNuclear arms controlxVerification. 0aNuclear nonproliferation. 0aNuclear reactorsxSecurity measures. 0aNuclear weaponsxSafety measures. 4aNuclear. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Nuclear.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEDP Sciences Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2020z978311075640140uhttps://doi.org/10.1051/978-2-7598-2072-6zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782759820726zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782759820726/original  a978-3-11-075640-1 EDP Sciences Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2020c2016d2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA